Telkom users can now continue enjoying services after the country's third-largest telecommunication operator announced resolving a network hitch. The network hitch saw the services interruptedÂ for more than 15 hours. The company has confirmed in a tweet that the services are back to normal. Users have been directed to restart their devices and share feedback. According to Telkom, the carrier was experiencing a service interruption that affected its GSM prepaid services and Global data. The users could not make calls, check balance, use T- kash, access the internet or send SMS. Telkom Kenya is one of the major telecommunications companies in Kenya and is government-owned.